.TH RUFUSARM64 1 "July 2026" "RufusArm64 0.10.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rufusarm64 \- graphical bootable USB creator for Ubuntu ARM64
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rufusarm64
.RI [ --persistence ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rufusarm64
opens the graphical RufusArm64 application. It creates raw Linux media and
supported Windows installation USB media after explicit target confirmation
and administrator authentication.
.PP
The ordinary Create USB action preserves supported Linux raw/ISOHybrid images
byte-for-byte. Persistent-live creation is a separate guarded workflow.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --persistence
Open the guarded persistent Ubuntu/Debian live-USB creator directly.
.SH SAFETY
Every selected target is erased. Verify the device model, capacity, and path
shown in the final confirmation dialog. A successful write or byte comparison
does not prove that particular firmware will boot the media.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rufusarm64-cli (1),
.BR rufusarm64-persistence (1)
